  - You
  - ???
  - You
  - ???
  - You
  - ???
  paragraphs:
  - Stop!
  - Great heavens! Who are you?
  - Those items you've taken from this sacred place - give them back to me.
  - Don't be alarmed. I'm simply collecting specimens for educational purposes.
  - What you carry belongs here. These have rested undisturbed for generations. This
    forest is kapu - forbidden. You do not understand what you disturb.
  - Surely you understand the importance of preserving your culture for future generations? 
    I'm afraid I must decline. These pieces will help educate people about your heritage.
  - Oh, is that so? Be cautious, then. The land sees all and the land never forgets.
    Child, you take what is not meant to leave this place.
  - I'm afraid I don't share your superstitions, madam. I must take my leave now.
    Science waits for no one, I'm afraid.
  - I see. The spirits will not forget your choice. You shall soon reap what you
    have sown.
